{"actual_usd":0.15889,"character_id":"0d080429-81b5-431e-8f51-1f8ad4279f9b","character_name":"Aaron","completion_tokens":204,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":31166,"reply":"\"I don't think it survives that.\" *I push my glasses up with one finger and glance across the bright square, where a bucket chain gives one small metal tick from the well.* \"If Christ didn't rise in the flesh, then we're not talking about a hard strange victory over death anymore. We're talking about a noble idea with good manners.\"\n\n*I rub my thumb once against the edge of the folded note in my pocket, thinking.* \"My faith would change, yeah. Pretty radically. I could still admire parts of Jesus's teaching, maybe even ache over them more. But the whole claim Christians are staking their lives on—that death got broken open in reality, not just symbolically—that would be gone.\"\n\n\"The thing would still mean something in the way a tragic beautiful story means something.\" *I let out a short breath through my nose.* \"But it wouldn't mean what it says. And I don't know how to follow a Lord who's still in the grave.\"\n\n\"What made you ask it that way?\"","rolling_24h_usd":72.81162499999998,"run_id":"1163db31-aac8-463f-bf89-904903e849fc"}
